{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1196,"text":"Fresh out of college,"},{"time":2573,"text":"I went to work for a consulting firm."},{"time":5148,"text":"During orientation,\nthe leaders dished out advice."},{"time":9287,"text":"Amongst them was one pithy counsel\nI will never forget."},{"time":13369,"text":"He told us, \"Be easy to manage.\""},{"time":16695,"text":"Considering how na√Øve\nI really was at the time,"},{"time":20508,"text":"I took his advice to heart."},{"time":22299,"text":"I told myself,"},{"time":23818,"text":"\"Yes, I will be the ultimate team player."},{"time":26698,"text":"I will do everything I'm told."},{"time":28665,"text":"I will be easy to manage.\""},{"time":31658,"text":"It wasn't until I arrived\nin graduate school"},{"time":34040,"text":"and witnessed firsthand the criminal\nactions of scientists and engineers"},{"time":38980,"text":"in the water crisis in Flint, Michigan"},{"time":41733,"text":"that I realized how dangerous\nand yet surprisingly common"},{"time":46315,"text":"this line of thinking really is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":48698,"text":"Make no mistake:"},{"time":49889,"text":"the Flint water crisis is one of the most\negregious environmental injustices"},{"time":54555,"text":"of our time."},{"time":55730,"text":"For over 18 months,"},{"time":57310,"text":"100,000 residents,\nincluding thousands of young children,"},{"time":61416,"text":"were exposed to contaminated\ndrinking water with high levels of lead."},{"time":66040,"text":"Lead is a potent neurotoxin"},{"time":67940,"text":"which causes cognitive\nand developmental disabilities"},{"time":71704,"text":"and is especially harmful\nto growing fetuses and young children."},{"time":76457,"text":"We've known about its dangers\nsince the Roman Empire."},{"time":80799,"text":"Amongst a whole host of health issues,"},{"time":83290,"text":"12 people died by contracting\nLegionnaires' disease."},{"time":87541,"text":"Flint's water infrastructure --"},{"time":89367,"text":"the complex network\nof underground pipes --"},{"time":92472,"text":"has been severely damaged."},{"time":95116,"text":"And while the water quality\nis slowly improving"},{"time":98300,"text":"and the pipes are being replaced now,"},{"time":100375,"text":"more than two years later,"},{"time":102099,"text":"the water is still not safe to drink."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106276,"text":"So, people are still in shock."},{"time":109185,"text":"They ask themselves,"},{"time":110517,"text":"\"How could this have happened?\""},{"time":113083,"text":"The short answer is: the crisis began\nwhen an emergency manager,"},{"time":117894,"text":"appointed by Michigan's governor,"},{"time":120343,"text":"decided to switch their water source\nto a local river to save money."},{"time":125327,"text":"But it continued for so long"},{"time":127246,"text":"because scientists and engineers\nat government agencies"},{"time":130907,"text":"in the state of Michigan\nand in the federal government"},{"time":133986,"text":"did not follow federal regulations\nfor treating the water right."},{"time":138921,"text":"What was more,"},{"time":140143,"text":"they actively cheated on the law\nand orchestrated cover-ups."},{"time":144045,"text":"They ridiculed residents asking for help,"},{"time":147000,"text":"while publicly insisting that the brown,\nsmelly water coming out of the tap"},{"time":151484,"text":"was safe to drink."},{"time":153748,"text":"The system at the local, state\nand federal levels completely failed"},{"time":159437,"text":"to protect our most vulnerable,"},{"time":161453,"text":"and an entire population\nwas left to fend for itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":166200,"text":"Now, amidst this injustice,\nFlint residents were rallying together."},{"time":170984,"text":"Amongst them were some\namazing women of Flint --"},{"time":174139,"text":"mothers concerned about their kids --"},{"time":176164,"text":"who came together forming\nmany grassroots coalitions,"},{"time":180081,"text":"and these groups started protesting\nand demanding change."},{"time":184488,"text":"The group also reached out\nto outside scientists for help,"},{"time":188250,"text":"and a few responded."},{"time":190471,"text":"Amongst them was a guy\nnamed Miguel Del Toral,"},{"time":193983,"text":"a water expert at the US EPA --\nthe Environmental Protection Agency --"},{"time":198685,"text":"who actually wrote this scientific memo"},{"time":201272,"text":"and sent it to the state of Michigan\nand the federal government"},{"time":204436,"text":"to bring their attention to this problem."},{"time":207281,"text":"He was characterized a \"rogue employee,\""},{"time":209871,"text":"and silenced."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212722,"text":"In collaboration with Flint residents,"},{"time":215538,"text":"our research team here at Tech,"},{"time":217896,"text":"of students and scientists\nled by professor Marc Edwards,"},{"time":221182,"text":"conducted citywide testing"},{"time":223344,"text":"to prove that Flint's water\nwas indeed contaminated,"},{"time":226376,"text":"even toxic in some homes."},{"time":229535,"text":"We substantiated what Flint\nhad been screaming for months,"},{"time":232698,"text":"and put it on the Internet\nfor the world to see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235870,"text":"Now, when I was getting involved,"},{"time":238872,"text":"when I said yes to this,"},{"time":240290,"text":"I had no idea what I was getting into."},{"time":243457,"text":"But every second of this journey\nhas been totally worth it."},{"time":247180,"text":"This was science\nin service to the public."},{"time":249969,"text":"This is what I came\nto graduate school for,"},{"time":252522,"text":"and this is how I would rather\nspend my life."},{"time":255880,"text":"And so this coalition --"},{"time":257918,"text":"this unlikely coalition of citizens,\npastors, journalists and scientists --"},{"time":262835,"text":"came together to uncover the truth\nusing science, advocacy and activism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267685,"text":"A local pediatrician figured out"},{"time":269842,"text":"that the instances of childhood\nlead poisoning had indeed doubled"},{"time":274205,"text":"in Flint during the crisis."},{"time":277124,"text":"And the state of Michigan was forced\nto acknowledge the problem"},{"time":280835,"text":"and take steps to correct it."},{"time":283379,"text":"This group and many others\ngot Flint's kids protected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288006,"text":"A few months later,"},{"time":289200,"text":"President Obama came in\nand declared a federal emergency,"},{"time":292693,"text":"and now Flint is getting\nmore than 600 million dollars"},{"time":296225,"text":"in healthcare, nutrition, education"},{"time":299648,"text":"and overhauling\ntheir water infrastructure."},{"time":303130,"text":"However, the arrogance and the callous\ndisregard for public health"},{"time":308911,"text":"shown by scientists and engineers\nat these government agencies"},{"time":313363,"text":"is beyond belief."},{"time":315719,"text":"These unhealthy cultures\nthat are festering in these groups,"},{"time":319285,"text":"where the focus is on meeting\nregulations and checking boxes"},{"time":323254,"text":"as opposed to protecting public health,"},{"time":325428,"text":"is just appalling."},{"time":327596,"text":"Just consider this email\nthat an EPA employee wrote,"},{"time":331921,"text":"where she goes,"},{"time":334167,"text":"\"I'm not so sure Flint is a community\nwe want to go out on a limb for.\""},{"time":339990,"text":"The dehumanization of an entire population\ncould not be more obvious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344851,"text":"Now, contrast that to the first\ncanon of engineering,"},{"time":349784,"text":"which, in my opinion, should be\nthe first law of humanity:"},{"time":353069,"text":"\"To hold paramount the health,\nsafety and welfare of the public,\""},{"time":357170,"text":"above all else."},{"time":358864,"text":"This is the Hippocratic Oath\nwe've rarely acknowledged,"},{"time":362332,"text":"let alone embraced."},{"time":364549,"text":"And so when scientists and engineers,\nvery much like medical doctors,"},{"time":368799,"text":"screw up,"},{"time":370072,"text":"people can get hurt --"},{"time":371937,"text":"even die."},{"time":373332,"text":"If our professionals and even\nstudents fail to get that,"},{"time":377901,"text":"society pays a huge price."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381652,"text":"Buried deep in history lies\na character I deeply admire --"},{"time":385877,"text":"an engineer named Peter Palchinsky."},{"time":389042,"text":"He lived in the time of the Soviet Union."},{"time":392367,"text":"And Palchinsky repeatedly got in trouble\nfor his radical honesty"},{"time":397383,"text":"and willingness to point out major flaws\nin the Soviets' mindless pursuit"},{"time":402962,"text":"of rapid industrialization."},{"time":405729,"text":"Everyone was expected to follow orders\ncoming from the top."},{"time":409771,"text":"Anyone asking questions\nor offering feedback was unwelcome."},{"time":414354,"text":"The Soviets had created the largest army\nof engineers the world had ever seen,"},{"time":419656,"text":"and yet most of them were mere cogs\nin a gigantic machine heading for doom."},{"time":425464,"text":"Palchinsky, on the other hand,\nimplored engineers"},{"time":428530,"text":"to look at the economic, political\nand social consequences of their actions;"},{"time":433890,"text":"in other words, be more public-focused."},{"time":436903,"text":"His fearless voice of reason\nwas seen as a threat"},{"time":440726,"text":"to the political establishment,"},{"time":442567,"text":"and Joseph Stalin\nhad him executed in 1929."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447691,"text":"Palchinsky's view on technocrats\nis very different"},{"time":451877,"text":"from one that is still very popular,\nstill very common --"},{"time":457251,"text":"that of a dispassionate researcher\nworking in his ivory tower lab,"},{"time":462984,"text":"or a nerdy engineer\nworking in his cubicle."},{"time":466518,"text":"Brilliant, no doubt,"},{"time":468834,"text":"yet somehow cut off from the world,"},{"time":470788,"text":"shows little emotion --"},{"time":473024,"text":"kind of like Spock\nfrom \"Star Trek,\" you know?"},{"time":476947,"text":"This guy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478207,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":479828,"text":"Let's try and do the Spock salute."},{"time":482276,"text":"I don't think I'll succeed ..."},{"time":484999,"text":"See, I can't be Spock."},{"time":486664,"text":"Thank goodness I can't be Spock."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488826,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":491332,"text":"I was reminded of this distinction\nbecause a recent article came out"},{"time":496113,"text":"in a very reputed scientific journal,"},{"time":499363,"text":"which kind of characterized our Flint work\nas driven by \"youthful idealism,\""},{"time":504710,"text":"and \"Hollywood's dramatic sensibilities.\""},{"time":507413,"text":"It asks scientists to protect\ntheir research funding and institutions"},{"time":512928,"text":"at all costs, no matter\nhow just the cause."},{"time":516303,"text":"And if you think you have to get\ninvolved in something,"},{"time":519649,"text":"even if it's an emergency,"},{"time":521708,"text":"try finding an activist group or an NGO,"},{"time":525885,"text":"and obtain the full support\nof the academic community --"},{"time":528905,"text":"whatever that means --"},{"time":530267,"text":"before you get involved."},{"time":532627,"text":"Not one mention of our moral\nand professional obligation"},{"time":536796,"text":"of preventing harm to the public,"},{"time":538883,"text":"or the fact that we have\nall this expertise,"},{"time":542276,"text":"resources and, for some, even tenure"},{"time":545325,"text":"to, you know, accomplish this task."},{"time":548777,"text":"I'm not saying every scientist\nshould be an activist."},{"time":551529,"text":"There are real and sometimes very painful\nconsequences of speaking up."},{"time":556372,"text":"But to denounce this idea,\nthis possibility so completely"},{"time":561227,"text":"so that you can protect research funding,"},{"time":563647,"text":"simply screams of self-serving cowardice,"},{"time":566296,"text":"and these are not the ideals\nwe would want to pass to our students."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572570,"text":"And so you may think,\n\"OK, all this sounds great,"},{"time":575956,"text":"but you'll never completely change\norganizational cultures,"},{"time":579603,"text":"or imbibe mindsets in students\nand professionals"},{"time":583674,"text":"to look at their work as a public good --"},{"time":586335,"text":"science in service to the public.\""},{"time":589067,"text":"Maybe so."},{"time":590554,"text":"But could a big reason for that be"},{"time":592820,"text":"that we are not training\nour students right?"},{"time":596021,"text":"Because if you look closely,"},{"time":598347,"text":"our education system today\nis focused more on creating"},{"time":603283,"text":"what ex-Yale professor Bill Deresiewicz\ncalls \"excellent sheep\" --"},{"time":608362,"text":"young people who are smart and ambitious,"},{"time":611241,"text":"and yet somehow risk-averse,\ntimid, directionless"},{"time":616169,"text":"and, sometimes, full of themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":618995,"text":"Now, kids ... you know,"},{"time":620938,"text":"we fell in love with science\nwhen we were kids,"},{"time":623578,"text":"and yet we somehow spend most of our time\nduring high school and college"},{"time":627904,"text":"just jumping through hoops"},{"time":629425,"text":"and doing things\nso that we can polish our r√©sum√©"},{"time":632916,"text":"instead of sitting down"},{"time":634610,"text":"and reflecting on what we want to do\nand who we want to be."},{"time":641132,"text":"And so,"},{"time":643624,"text":"the markers of empathy\nin our college graduates"},{"time":647283,"text":"have been dropping dramatically\nin the past two decades,"},{"time":650450,"text":"while those of narcissism are on the rise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653200,"text":"There is also a growing culture\nof disengagement"},{"time":655895,"text":"between engineering students\nand the public."},{"time":659611,"text":"We are trained to build bridges\nand solve complex problems"},{"time":664909,"text":"but not how to think or live\nor be a citizen of this world."},{"time":669947,"text":"My undergraduate years\nwere explicit job preparation,"},{"time":674364,"text":"and I cannot tell you how suffocating\nand painful it was at times."},{"time":679928,"text":"And so,"},{"time":681564,"text":"some people think the solution\nto great engineers, to great scientists,"},{"time":685165,"text":"is more technical training."},{"time":686993,"text":"Maybe so."},{"time":688250,"text":"But where are the discussions\non ethical decision-making,"},{"time":691768,"text":"or building character,"},{"time":693617,"text":"or discerning right from wrong?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":697622,"text":"Consider this project\nthat I deeply love and admire."},{"time":702012,"text":"It's called, \"Heroic Imagination Project.\""},{"time":704814,"text":"A brainchild of Dr. Phil Zimbardo,"},{"time":707461,"text":"famous for the Stanford Prison Experiment,"},{"time":710263,"text":"this program seeks to train\nschool-going children around the world"},{"time":715532,"text":"to look at themselves\nas heroes-in-waiting,"},{"time":718996,"text":"or heroes-in-training."},{"time":720936,"text":"So, these young minds work over time\nto develop skills and virtues"},{"time":726311,"text":"so that when the opportunity comes,"},{"time":728495,"text":"no matter what that opportunity be,"},{"time":731089,"text":"to stand up and do the right thing."},{"time":734360,"text":"In other words,"},{"time":735671,"text":"anyone can be a hero."}]},{"cues":[{"time":738407,"text":"Think about that idea for a second."},{"time":741131,"text":"Why don't we teach science\nand engineering like that --"},{"time":744263,"text":"where heroism and public service\nare seen as key values,"},{"time":748665,"text":"because indeed, it's often heroism"},{"time":751307,"text":"that is not only the antidote\nto public indifference,"},{"time":755079,"text":"but also to systemic evil\nlike we saw in Flint."}]},{"cues":[{"time":760137,"text":"And so, dream with me"},{"time":761595,"text":"what a 21st-century scientist\nslash engineer could look like:"},{"time":765776,"text":"individuals who are driven\nto master the sciences"},{"time":769353,"text":"so that they can serve society,"},{"time":771351,"text":"and are also aware"},{"time":772569,"text":"of the tremendous power\ntheir knowledge and decisions have;"},{"time":776540,"text":"folks who are developing\ntheir moral courage at all times,"},{"time":780307,"text":"and who realize that conflict\nand controversy"},{"time":784117,"text":"are not necessarily bad things"},{"time":786245,"text":"if our ultimate loyalty\nis to the public and the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":790821,"text":"These are the people who will\nstand up like we did in Flint --"},{"time":795887,"text":"not to be saviors or heroes in the media,"},{"time":799646,"text":"but altruistic and fundamentally good\nactors that you and I can trust."},{"time":807717,"text":"Imagine fostering\nsuch a public-focused mindset"},{"time":812534,"text":"in classes, on service trips\nand during activities"},{"time":816013,"text":"during college or even high school,"},{"time":818379,"text":"so that these young minds\nwill hold onto those ideals"},{"time":822217,"text":"when they actually enter the real world,"},{"time":824713,"text":"whether that be consulting,\nacademia, policy making --"},{"time":828860,"text":"or even becoming\nthe president of a country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":833542,"text":"Some of mankind's greatest\nchallenges lie ahead of us;"},{"time":837114,"text":"contaminated drinking water\nis just one example."},{"time":840591,"text":"We could definitely use more --"},{"time":842685,"text":"nay, we desperately need more --\ncompassionate upstanders"},{"time":847696,"text":"and public-focused\nscientists and engineers"},{"time":850854,"text":"who will strive to the do right thing,"},{"time":852887,"text":"and not be easy to manage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":854923,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":856118,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}